Description: Round-topped limestone stela with a raised border and two registers: Upper: Scene of the deceased woman before an offering-table worshipping Ra enthroned and Isis; winged sun-disc and five columns of Hieroglyphic text above. Lower: Six rows of Hieroglyphic text.
Curator's comments: To be published by Karl Jansen-Winkeln
Acquisition name: Donated through: Dr Henry Bence Jones
